{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pulls/110","id":3713514512,"node_id":"PR_kwDOQTKhm87dV7wQ","html_url":"https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/110","diff_url":"https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/110.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/110.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/issues/110","number":110,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"hnerv_fec6_fixed_huffman_k16","user":{"login":"adpena","id":10686801,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNjg2ODAx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10686801?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena","html_url":"https://github.com/adpena","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/adpena/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"# archive.zip\n\nHosted at: `https://github.com/adpena/comma_video_compression_challenge/releases/download/fec6-frontier-submission-20260520/archive.zip` (GitHub Release on `adpena/comma_video_compression_challenge`).\n\n- SHA-256: `6bae0201fb082457a02c69565531aba4c5942669c384fdc48e7d554f7b893fcf`\n- Size: 178,517 bytes (single ZIP member `x`, 178,417 bytes, stored uncompressed at `compression_type=0` / `ZIP_STORED`).\n- Runtime tree (`inflate.sh`, `inflate.py`, `src/codec.py`, `src/codec_sidecar.py`, `src/frame_selector.py`, `src/model.py`) is staged directly in this PR under [`submissions/hnerv_fec6_fixed_huffman_k16`](https://github.com/adpena/comma_video_compression_challenge/tree/ec6cc7f98c16b6ad2db8bc7cde65757bb7993004/submissions/hnerv_fec6_fixed_huffman_k16) at head `ec6cc7f98c16b6ad2db8bc7cde65757bb7993004`, alongside `archive.zip` per the upstream contract.\n\n# report.txt\n\nGenerated by `upstream/evaluate.py --device cpu` on a Linux x86_64 host. Pose, segmentation, and rate components are included.\n\n# eval host info\n\nCPU eval ran on a Modal Linux x86_64 container (Ubuntu, no GPU; upstream evaluator report shows `num_threads: 2`, matching the `ubuntu-latest` GHA runner family). Paired CUDA eval ran on a Modal NVIDIA Tesla T4 against the same `archive.zip` bytes.\n\n# build cost info\n\nTraining is one-shot per video on a single GPU; final training-stage compute used Modal A100. A100 is mentioned here as training compute only, NOT auth-eval hardware.\n\n# does your submission require gpu for evaluation (inflation)?\n\nno\n\n# did you include the compression script? and want it to be merged?\n\nno\n\n# changes from upstream\n\nFEC6 selector bolt-on around the public HNeRV lineage. The HNeRV decoder in `src/model.py` originates in PR [#95](https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/95) by `@AaronLeslie138` (`hnerv_muon`) and is byte-identical here. The byte substrate is PR [#101](https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/101) by `@SajayR` (`hnerv_ft_microcodec`), inheriting its compact decoder, latent-payload parsing, Brotli-coded source streams, and canonical Huffman for the latent sidecar. Prior lineage: PR [#98](https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/98) (`@EthanYangTW`), PR [#100](https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/100) (`@BradyMeighan`), PR [#102](https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/102), PR [#103](https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/103) (`@rem2`). This packet does not import PR #103's `constriction` range coder.\n\nNew in this packet: a 31-mode per-frame transform selector (K=16 active palette) chosen offline against the upstream scorer + a fixed-Huffman k=16 codebook over the selector indices. Selector framework is ~265 LOC of Python (`src/frame_selector.py`). Member `x` wraps the PR #101 source payload as `FP11 + source_len + source_pr101_payload + selector_len + selector_payload`; PR #101's Brotli envelope is unchanged and operates only inside the source-payload region, not at the ZIP layer and not over the appended FEC6 selector bitstream. Archive byte delta vs PR #101 source is +259 bytes (rate cost `25 * 259 / 37545489 = 0.000172`).\n\n# additional comments\n\nSubmitted by Alejandro Peña <adpena@gmail.com>. Submission name follows the `hnerv_<descriptor>` convention from PR #95 `hnerv_muon` / PR #101 `hnerv_ft_microcodec`. Thanks to @YassineYousfi for keeping the leaderboard open and clarifying the late-submission rubric (PR [#108](https://github.com/commaai/comma_video_compression_challenge/pull/108) closure). Thanks to @AaronLeslie138, @EthanYangTW, @BradyMeighan, @SajayR, and @rem2 — the HNeRV decoder used here is reused byte-identically from PR #95, and the entropy-coded selector pattern is downstream of the discipline established across the PR #95 → #98 → #100 → #101 → #102 → #103 chain.\n\n**Where this sits.** This packet hits a within-HNeRV-family local floor. PR #95 / #98 / #100 / #101 / #102 / #103 / this packet cluster within ~0.0008 on the CPU axis. CPU `0.192051 [contest-CPU]` is `−0.000794` vs PR #101 GOLD at `0.192845` (already includes the +259-byte rate cost); paired CUDA `0.226210 [contest-CUDA T4]`. For the tested frontier/medalist HNeRV-family archives, post-hoc general-purpose recompression of the actual contest `archive.zip` member bytes has no deliverable rate-term gain. To lower the contest-score frontier from here, the path likely runs through the full compression stack: pretraining and data priors; training objectives, curriculum, and scorer-aware search; architecture/substrate changes; quantization and post-training adaptation; entropy coding and archive grammar; decoder-side side information; and principled composition across those layers, not post-hoc recompression of the same member bytes. For maintainers and readers who want the broader research context: class/substrate-shift research lives in `comma-lab`: [`active candidate inventory`](https://github.com/adpena/comma-lab/blob/b7f16a081ee381803dd5d917bdaf805453fb81f3/docs/asymptotic_floor_candidate_inventory.md) and [`full-stack source map`](https://github.com/adpena/comma-lab/blob/b7f16a081ee381803dd5d917bdaf805453fb81f3/docs/full_stack_source_map.md), and reusable research tooling lives in [`adpena/tac`](https://github.com/adpena/tac). The submitted runtime in this PR is self-contained aside from stdlib, `torch`, `numpy`, and `brotli`, and does not depend on those repositories.","created_at":"2026-05-20T03:28:56Z","updated_at":"2026-05-20T14:00:48Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"8fa62958b0d4dd8fdf59a1348795977475f7faaf","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[{"login":"YassineYousfi","id":29985433,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5OTg1NDMz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/29985433?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi","html_url":"https://github.com/YassineYousfi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/YassineYousfi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.git